name: Beaver Cafe
directions: At the back of the restaurant there are two genderfree singe washrooms. Not wheelchair accessible, about half a dozen stairs to go up.
comment: Yes, it's a restaurant so it normally might be weird to walk in to use the washroom, but since they're very trans friendly they would probably be very understanding of someone needing to pee in a safe space.

name: Rhode Island College, Gaige Hall
directions: Second floor in the left wing.  There are two women's bathrooms, one men's and one non-gendered, all single stall.

name: Ben and Jerry's
directions: upper level, where the counter is.

name: Elliot's Martini Bar
directions: Mostly straight shot to back of bar, small hallway, doors on right. First door is women's, second door is men's. Single person with locking door.
comment: Gay friendly staff and most patrons as well. Slightly more upscale bar, almost certainly will card on weekends. Often very crowded on weekends. You should buy something if you can.

name: East Coast Bar
directions: straight shot from front door all the way to the back of the bar, right and left doors are bathrooms (center door leads to outside).
comment: Both are very large locking bathrooms, single person, one door, non-gendered. This is a bar, so you should buy something, even a soda or water, and there is a possibility you will be asked for id to verify you are 21. Staff is mostly gay friendly, patrons are so-so, but I have never had trouble.

name: Cineplex Galaxy
directions: Two accessible washrooms are available on either side of the multiplex. Staff can direct you to them once you show them a movie ticket.
comment: This tends to be the busiest movie theatre complex in Canada, so don't be surprised if they're occupied on a Friday or Saturday night.

name: Brewster Town Hall
directions: Single bathrooms inside rear entrance next to tourist information center.

name: Hartman's Independent Grocers
directions: Ask for a key.

name: Uncommon Grounds Cafe
directions: Enter cafe and turn left.  There is a door along the wall to your left, go through it, the bathroom is gender free and child friendly on your right.
comment: This is a small queer friendly cafe.  It isn't always busy so you might feel more comfortable buying a coffee after using their restroom - but it's probably not a requirement.

name: Padgett Station
directions: Go through the door way past the coffee bean shelf and there are two individual restrooms.
comment: Monday - Thursday 9:00 am - 11:00 pm  Friday - Saturday  9:00 am - midnight Sunday  9:00 am - 5:00 pm

name: UNC, Peabody Hall
street: UNC,School of Education,  CB# 3500, Peabody Hall
directions: Enter the building through the main entrance, which is on Cameron Avenue. On the first floor there is a gender neutral bathroom on your right when you past the elevator.

name: California Adventure - Bugs Land
directions: In the 'Bugs land' in california Adventure, there is a 'family' restroom which is not gendered.
comment: Some non-gendered bathrooms are in place throughout the park.

name: The Barbeque Joint
directions: Walk in and it's directly to the left.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Located at the back middle of the store by shoes.
comment: There are men's, women's, and family bathrooms.  The family bathroom is a large single locking bathroom.

name: Polynesian Beach & Golf Resort
directions: go into lobby into next room its the second door on the left.

name: Moe's
directions: On the third floor.  You need a token from the cashier's desk.

name: Cafe Mediterraneum
directions: Get the key at the counter; up the stairs and to your left.

name: La Paloma Sabanera
directions: In the back, past the food counter
comment: Often closes by 530 or 6 pm. Is close to the Capital and legislative buildings. About 20 minute walk from downtown Hartford. Trans Friendly.

name: YMCA Berkeley - Gym
directions: The single-stall bathroom, once you're in the building, is on the same floor as the entrance.  There may be another one on a different floor as well.
comment: This resource is mostly for gym members.  If you aren't a member, it might take explaining yourself, but the staff are usually pretty kind.

name: King Solomon's Reef
directions: This bathroom is inside the old card room. Just ask a server to use it.

name: Del Mar Theater
directions: First floor.
comment: Ask emp. first- I manage here (FTM), trans friendly

name: Oberlin College Student Union
directions: 2nd floor and 3rd floor, gender neutral bathrooms with stalls, up the stairs and to the left. There's a large step up to get inside.
comment: This bathroom is labeled \\\"gender neutral.\\\"  There are many other bathrooms throughout campus (particularly in dorms) which have been informally voted by residents to be gender-free.

name: Naropa University
directions: This is on the Naropa University Campus.  There are three gender free bathrooms.  Two are in the Library.  The other is at the top floor of the Lincoln building.

name: JIFFI STOP
directions: JIFFI STOP - Michigan Public Rest Area.South-West corner of M6 and Kalamazoo Avenue.
comment: JIFFI is an acronym for Jons Installed at Fast Freeway Intersections. JIFFI is an interesting design, being embedded right into the corner of the M6-Kalamazoo bridge abuttment.  JIFFI also offers the added convenience of wireless Internet access.

name: Market Street Coffee
comment: Possibly one of the prettiest bathrooms in Chapel Hill, it's just a one-room with a lock that has a gorgeous decorative finish.

name: UNC LGBTQ Center
directions: The UNC LGBTQ Center, currently located in the basement of Steele building, has a single-occupancy, accessible bathroom.
comment: Steele Building is usually unlocked from 9AM -5PM Monday - Friday.

name: HRC Building
directions: Located on first floor.
comment: Not a "public" bathroom per se but anyone attending a function or visiting/touring the building has access to it.

name: University of Illinois Student Union
directions: Rest rooms on each floor.  If driving, parking in front with meters.
comment: Always open.

name: UNC-CH Campus Mitchel Hall
directions: Basement floor next to the elevator
comment: Small bathroom

name: Richmond Friends Meeting (Quakers)
directions: Two bathrooms on first floor, one on second floor.
comment: It's not really open to the public, but if there is an event going on that you are attending, the bathrooms are great - private, non-gendered, and accessable.  There's even an elevator to the second floor.  It would be a good place to rent out (cheap) for a meeting or event.

name: Allen County Public Library
directions: Second floor right off east elevators.
comment: Library staff is non-judgemental.

name: Monopole
directions: Two unisex bathrooms; one on the first level, one upstairs
comment: Open 5pm-2am; if you were to stop in Plattsburgh at least once in your life, the Monopole is pretty much THE bar you would want to hang out at. Very chill atmosphere; dudes and girls share the same bathroom and everyone's cool with that. Though some people in the North Country are incredulous at the thought: "OMG I can't believe this is a shared bathroom!" But they get over it.

name: Finfine Ethiopian
directions: inside the restaurant towards the back. a very spacious bathroom, no gender indicated.
comment: great food, super friendly people.

name: Blake's on Telegraph
directions: Immediately on your right as you go in the door there is a set of stairs.  Just make a beeline down those stairs and straight to the back.  There is usually no one downstairs to see you.

name: JJ Bean Coffee
directions: Front Door - past cashier, head to back & around the corner (turn right). Side door - turn left then right. Two gender free bathrooms available
comment: early am to 9pm-ish 7 days/week

name: Simone de Beavoir Institute
comment: 1) There is one single stall washroom in the classroom on the main floor (normally ok to use if there's not a class happening)2) A single stall on the second floor there is a conference room (same thing as before...if nothings going on okay to use)3) A single stall on the 4th floor at the Reading Room

name: Coffee Society
directions: walk parallel to the counter toward the back, and make a right down the hall.
comment: gender-neutral and single-stall, usually pretty clean.

name: Wylie E. Groves High School
directions: Two bathrooms exist like this--one in the athletic wing, and one in the music wing, nearby. Both are towards the north end of the building.

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Go inside and go to the right, down a short hall.
comment: There's often a short wait.

name: Whole Foods
directions: Walk in and go straight to the very back of the building.
comment: Open till 10 pm.  Very safe - I often use the men's if the women's is busy.  They're both "one-seaters."

name: parel
street: 36 b, dr. rk. shirodkar mar, near itc hotel,

name: Center for LGBT Health/Kaladi Bros. coffee
directions: Queerly gendered restroom. Two single stall locking restrooms labeled Kenneth and Barb, both drag queen barbie dolls. It is safe to use either restroom

name: Seattle LGBT Community Center
directions: Past the front desk on the left side, just after the kitchen.
comment: Open Monday - Saturday: 10am-9pm, Sunday: 11am - 8pm(all hours are subject to volunteer staffing availability)

name: Meijer's
directions: Non-gendered locking washroom near the pharacy and customer service.

name: VAMC
directions: First floor, near Chappel
comment: Veterans Hospital, be discreete.  24/7

name: Texas State University
directions: Laurel Hall: Lobby

name: Texas State University
directions: Brandon Hall: 2nd floor lobby

name: Texas State University
directions: Beretta Hall: 3rd floor lobby

name: Texas State University
directions: Lampasas: 4th floor

name: Texas State University
directions: Theatre Building: 1st floor

name: Texas State University
directions: Commons Dining Hall: To the right of the entrance

name: Texas State University
directions: Admissions Building: 1st and 2nd floors

name: Texas State University
directions: LBJ Student Center: 3rd floor

name: Texas State University
directions: Student Health Center: 1st and 2nd floors
comment: The 1st floor lobby bathrooms can be seen by patients in the waiting area.

name: Affirmations
directions: Gender free in basement accessed by stairs or elevator.  Gendered on first floor, easily accessible from rear entrance.
comment: LGBT community centerMonday-Wednesday, 9am-9pmThursday, 9am-11pmFriday-Saturday, 9am-midnightFriday and Saturday late at night may be restricted to youth.  Doors may automatically lock at 9pm on all nights.Staff doesn't care which gendered bathroom you use.

name: Prontos
directions: Genderfree unisex located next to manager's office. Enter in rear from Sixth. First door from street. You're entering lounge/pool table room from the rear.
comment: Caution: Prontos is a mid to upscale open lgbt bar and restaurant.  Open seven days a week, often from early morning to late, late at night.

name: Societe des Arts Technologiques
directions: Two bathrooms, the one behind the bar is prolly wheelchair-accessible. There's a larger one in the basement.
comment: since its a concert venue, you need to have a ticket to enter, duh.

name: Bridgewater commons Mall
comment: This is a uni gender restroom if ... it remains unlocked!

name: Pembroke Public Library
directions: Located on the 2nd floor. Ask for key at main desk.

name: Grande Bibliothèque du Québec
directions: If entering from the metro or from boul. De Maisonneuve, walk along the entire lobby to the rear of the building. The bathrooms by the café and lockers have two conventional m/f stalled washrooms, and a locking disabled-accessible non-gendered washroom. Warning: the other washrooms in the building (i.e. in the library stacks) are m/f stalled with no separate single locking bathroom.
comment: Montreal's central library and the national library of Quebec. Connected directly to Berri-UQAM metro. Across the street from the main bus terminal and Berri Square. Boul. De Maisonneuve x rue Berri.

name: Bržlerie St-Denis
directions: Basement (go down stairs to the rear of the upper level, near the kitchen)
comment: Coffee shop in the Quartier Latin. Try the café Dante. Saint-Denis at de Maisonneuve, Berri-UQAM metro.

name: Cha Noir
directions: Rear of the tea house.
comment: Tea house serving tea and light desserts and selling loose tea, teapots, and other teaware.

name: Japanese Garden Coffeehouse
directions: to your left as you enter the building
comment: It's a really pretty stop if you're in the middle of a bike ride.  Be sure to go visit the koi pond in back!

name: Clover Building
directions: 2nd floor all the way in back. The police will be called.Restrooms for tenants only
comment: Building is open 8am-8pm Mon-Fri and 9am-6pm Saturdays. Not open Sundays. It's a funky old building full of offices, nobody will question you.

name: TR Video
comment: 8am-3am 365 days a year.

name: Kilo
directions: Rear of the restaurant. Two gendered, locking bathrooms.
comment: Village mainstay (sandwiches, coffee, etc.) at the corner of Sainte-Catherine and Alexandre-De Sève, across from Sky. Metro Beaudry or Papineau.

name: Ala Moana Shopping Center
directions: Ground floor next to center stageMall level next to Banana Republic
comment: Both are family bathrooms which can be locked

name: Redwing Bar & Grill
directions: In the back towards the smoking patio.
comment: This is a primarily gay/lesbian bar and no one cares who uses which restroom! They are single stall, door locked restrooms.

name: Petco Park
directions: Family restrooms throughout the stadium for anyone to use.

name: La Jolla Shores Beach
street: 5390 La Jolla Blvd (near this address @ the beach)
directions: Public bathrooms down at the shoreline.

name: San Diego Zoo
directions: Once in the zoo, go to the left and it is near the Skyfari.
comment: It is a "Family" restroom, so males, females, or androgynous folks can use.

name: Shooterz
directions: Bathrooms in the back.
comment: Not great for the differently-abled

name: Syracuse University Law School
directions: From faculty parking and the quad enter into law school under walkbridge to the left.  Follow hallway to the right and then to the left - bathrooms are just after the left on the life side of the hall.
comment: You can get into this building during school hours - after dark it's ID restricted to law students.VERY large rooms.

name: Syracuse University Law School
directions: From faculty parking and the quad enter into law school under walkbridge to the left.  Follow hallway to the right and then to the left - bathrooms are just after the left on the life side of the hall.
comment: You can get into this building during school hours - after dark it's ID restricted to law students.VERY large rooms.

name: Univ. of Denver Law School
directions: Every level of the library on the east wall.
comment: There are locking gendered bathrooms and  unisex, handicap accessible bathrooms.

name: Mystic River Park
street: Mystic River Park off Cottrell St.
comment: 24 hour Public rest room

name: Redmond Regional Library
directions: Inside the entrance hall
comment: Open weekdays 10 to 9, Saturdays noon to 6 and Sunday 10 to 5

name: tHERe Coffee Shop
directions: Bathroom is along back wall.
comment: This is a lesbian owned coffee shop and bar.

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Back of store on the left.

name: Pete's University Park Cafe
directions: Take a left at the cash register and then a right.

name: Common Grounds
directions: Walk past counter to back of shop.
comment: There are two bathrooms.

name: Lincoln Square Cinemas
directions: Enter through main entrance (theatre is on third floor). There is a hallway to the left with more theatres (#1-10 or something like that) and the bathroom is down that hallway on the right side.
comment: Unfortunately, the bathroom IS past the ticket gate so unless the person collecting tickets is nice and lets you use the bathroom, you may have to buy a movie ticket. However, GREAT theatre to go to! No need to worry about using the bathroom in the middle of a movie!

name: Cafe Verde / Peoples Food Coop
directions: Back between the cafe and the hot bar there are two single stall locking bathrooms.  If you're waiting, there's a huge wall of local news and information on the bulletin board nearby.
comment: 7am-10pm most days.  Nice spot.

name: Manpuku
directions: First floor, bathroom is at back of restaurant

name: Stata Center, MIT
directions: Every floor has two single stall bathrooms, each paired with a multistall bathroom; in MIT parlance the single stall bathroom has a room number 32-Dx03 or 32-Gx58, where x is the floor number between 3 and 9 and D or G is the Dreyfoos or Gates tower. Each bathroom is near a bank of elevators, sometimes behind it.
comment: Open only during the week, slightly longer than buisness hours, though if one knows how to enter MIT main campus via other routes, they are 24hr accessible.

name: Mountain Equipment Co-op
directions: Main floor of the store, is a male/female/babychange single, locking

name: Kmart
directions: Near the in-store restaurant.

name: Audubon Circle
directions: Two genderfree bathrooms.
comment: Nice bar!

name: Bella Luna Restaurant
directions: Past take-out window of restaurant, in Brewery Complex building lobby.

name: Crate and Barrel
directions: 2nd floor. Walk towards back left of the building, by the windows.
comment: Mon-Fri: 	10 am - 9 pmSaturday:    	10 am - 9 pmSunday: 	11 am - 6 pm

name: womens center
directions: Main floor past reception, to the right

name: Teany Cafe
directions: One locking bathroom.
comment: 10am-11pm sunday-thursday,10am-1am on fridays and saturdays

name: Gobo
street: 401 avenue of the americas (between waverly place & 8th street)
directions: In the back, the two doors are completely unmarked -- not even a WC.
comment: Restaurant open 7 days a week, 11:30AM - 11:00PM

name: Cafe Istria
directions: The flirting bit isn't actually necessary, but pretty much all the employees are flirt-worthy anyway.  In any case, you just have to ask at the counter for a key.
comment: Monday - Friday: 6:30 AM - 7:00 PMSaturday: 7:00 AM - 7:00 PMSunday: 8:00 AM - 6:00 PMFree wi-fi with purchase.  Fabulous gelato.
